===Noun===
'''dean''' (''plural'' '''[[deans]]''')

# a senior [[official]] in a [[college]] or [[university]], who may be in charge of a division or [[faculty]] (for example, the ''dean of science'') or have some other advisory or [[disciplinary]] function (for example, the ''dean of students'')
#a [[dignitary]] or [[preside|presiding]] officer in certain [[church]]  bodies, especially an ecclesiastical dignitary, [[subordinate]] to a bishop.
# the [[senior]] member of some group of people
#*''dean of the diplomatic corps'' - a country's most senior [[ambassador]]
#*''dean of the House'' - the longest-serving member of a [[legislature]]

